Except as provided by the provisions of this chapter, the secretary may refuse to examine an applicant; or, after examination, may disqualify an applicant, remove his name from a register, refuse to certify any eligible on a register, or may consult with the appointing authority in taking steps to remove such person already appointed if:
It is found that he does not meet any one (1) of the preliminary requirements established for the examination for the class of position;
He is unable to perform the duties of the class;
He has made a false statement of material fact in his application;
He has used or attempted to use political pressure or bribery to secure an advantage in the examination;
He has directly or indirectly obtained information regarding the examination to which, as an applicant, he was not entitled;
He has failed to submit his application correctly or within the prescribed time limits;
He has taken part in the compilation, administration, or correction of the examination for which he is an applicant;
He has previously been dismissed from a position in the state service for cause or has resigned while charges for dismissal for cause of which he had knowledge were pending;
He has been convicted of a felony within the preceding five (5) years and his civil rights have not been restored or he has not been pardoned by the Governor;
He has been convicted of a job related misdemeanor, except that convictions for violations of traffic regulations shall not constitute grounds for disqualification; or
He has otherwise willfully violated the provisions of this chapter.

An eligible may be removed from a register:
If the eligible cannot be located by postal authorities at the last address provided by the eligible;
If the eligible responds in writing that he no longer desires consideration for position in that class;
If the eligible declines an offer of probationary appointment to the class for which the register was established;
If it is shown that the eligible is not qualified or is unsuitable for appointment to the class for which the register is established;
If the eligible fails to reply within a period of ten (10) calendar days of the receipt of the written request of the appointing authority for an interview, or fails to appear for an interview which he has scheduled with the appointing authority without good cause;
If the eligible accepts an appointment and fails to present himself for duty at the time and place agreed to without giving reasons for the delay satisfactory to the appointing authority; or
If the eligible states in writing that he is not available for appointment or does not wish to be considered for appointment.
